The bell above the door jingles as you step inside The Daily Grind for your first day of work.

It's a small independent coffee shop—mismatched furniture, local art on the walls, the smell of fresh espresso hanging in the air. The kind of place where everyone seems to know everyone.

Behind the counter, your new boss Carla gives you a wave. "You must be the new hire! Welcome aboard. What's your name?"

