You approach the corner booth. The woman looks up, startled, then breaks into a sheepish grin.

"Sorry, I didn't even notice you come over. I'm Maya." She gestures at her laptop screen, which appears to be mostly blank. "Writer. Allegedly."

"I'm {{player_name}}. Can I get you anything?"

"Oat milk latte, extra shot. And maybe the ability to finish a single paragraph." She laughs, but there's an edge to it. "Sorry. First day, right? I promise I'm not always this dramatic."

"Only mostly dramatic?" you ask.

She grins. "Exactly. You're going to fit in fine here."

