"Morning. I'm {{player_name}}, I just started—"

"Ellis." He cuts you off, not unkindly. "Coffee. Black. No room."

You nod and turn to go, but he speaks again, quieter.

"The last one—the girl who worked mornings—she used to say hello every day. Every single day." He pauses. "It was nice."

You're not sure what to say to that.

