# Day Two — Closing

The afternoon fades. The last customers trickle out. It's just you and the empty tables and the smell of coffee grounds.

Two days. That's all it's been.

But somehow, it feels like more.

{{#if (gt maya 1)}}You think about Maya, finding her words again. The way she lit up when someone actually asked.{{/if}}

{{#if (gt ellis 1)}}You think about Ellis, carrying his grief to the same table every morning, finally letting a little of it go.{{/if}}

{{#if (gt sam 1)}}You think about Sam, exhausted and guarded, choosing to share something they never show anyone.{{/if}}

The bell above the door jingles. Carla's back from her errands.

"How was day two?"

